CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 21, 1964, pg. 6 reads: "Cutting Cake - Mr. and Mrs. Earl Dilliard Jr. cut the first slice of their wedding cake, after their recent marriage. The bride is the former Mildred Elaine Buchaum, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Fred Buchaum.  The wedding took place in home of the groom's parents. Mr. and Mrs. Earl Dilliard Sr. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of groom Earl Dilliard Jr. and bride Mildred Elaine Buchaum Dilliard, cutting wedding cake in home of Mr. and Mrs. Earl Dilliard Sr. with strawberry patterned curtains
